c4 Harbor Authority — Manifest API Components

tag Technology as tech
  Express blue
  TypeScript green
  PostgreSQL purple
  Redis red

Ship Captain is a person
  description: Files cargo manifests and books berths
  -Files manifests via [HTTPS]-> Manifest API

Harbor Authority is a system
  description: Manages berths, manifests, and tolls for the port

  containers
    Manifest API is a container tech: Express
      description: Core API for berths, manifests, and tolls

      components
        Berth Controller is a component tech: Express
          description: Handles berth booking and release requests
          -Validates payloads with-> Manifest Validator
          -Reads and writes berths via-> Ledger Repository

        Manifest Validator is a component tech: TypeScript
          description: Checks cargo manifests against port rules

        Toll Calculator is a component tech: TypeScript
          description: Tallies doubloon tolls per berth and cargo
          -Persists receipts via-> Ledger Repository

        Tide Gateway is a component tech: TypeScript
          description: Wraps calls to the external tide almanac
          -Caches forecasts in-> Chart Cache

        Ledger Repository is a component tech: TypeScript
          description: Data-access layer over the harbor ledger
          -Reads and writes [SQL/TCP]-> Harbor Ledger

    Harbor Ledger is a container is a database tech: PostgreSQL
      description: Berths, manifests, tariffs, and toll receipts

    Chart Cache is a container is a cache tech: Redis
      description: Tide tables and berth-availability cache
